        "description": "The National Institute of Agronomic Studies and Research (INERA) is a higher education institution based in Kinshasa, Democratic Republic of the Congo. It specializes in agricultural engineering, biological sciences, and earth sciences. In addition to its headquarters in Kinshasa, it has research stations in M'vuazi (Kongo Central), Gandajika (Lomami), Yangambi (Tshopo), Nioka (Ituri), and Mulungu (South Kivu)."
